  "answer": "**Manusmṛti 10.97** captures *svadharma* as the operative concept: \"Better one's own Dharma, even if imperfect, than another's well-performed. For one who lives by the Dharma of another falls immediately from his caste.\"[^1]\n\nHere, \"one's own Dharma\" translates *svadharma*, the duty proper to one's birth (*varna*) and station.[^2] An English-only reader must mentally unpack and re-stitch this each time:\n\n- **Birth (*varna*)**: Duties are assigned at birth to the four *varṇas* (Brahmin from the mouth, Kṣatriya from arms, Vaiśya from thighs, Śūdra from feet).[^3] A Brahmin's *svadharma* is the \"six occupations\" like teaching and Vedic study; a Śūdra's sole duty is serving the others.[^4][^5]\n- **Station (role/occupation)**: *Svadharma* locks one to varṇa-specific acts. Brahmins \"abide in their own duties\" via teaching/sacrificing; Vaiśyas via trade/agriculture.[^6] Violating this (e.g., lower *varṇa* usurping higher occupations) merits banishment.[^7]\n- **Obligation (performance)**: Even imperfect adherence to *svadharma* upholds caste; perfect execution of alien *dharma* destroys it. This prioritizes innate station over skill.[^8]\n\nWithout *svadharma*'s compression, the reader toggles between scattered rules on *varṇas*, duties, and penalties—reassembling the nexus of birth-station-obligation per mention. The Sanskrit noun fuses what English fragments across verses.\n\n[^1]: Manu, *Manusmṛti*, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/10/translation/#p-53206d).\n[^2]: Ibid., [paragraphs](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/10/translation/#p-53206d).\n[^3]: Ibid., Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/01/translation/#p-71a5c2).\n[^4]: Ibid., Chapter 10, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/10/translation/#p-26a572).\n[^5]: Ibid., Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/01/translation/#p-26a572).\n[^6]: Ibid., Chapter 10, [paragraphs](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/10/translation/#p-2ec902).\n[^7]: Ibid., Chapter 10, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/10/translation/#p-7cad60).\n[^8]: Ibid., Chapter 10, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/10/translation/#p-53206d).",
